 the following are true:<br>
<br>
1) Compatibility and collision issues due to the DirectX 9 changes on Beta made it difficult to effectively test content<br>
2) Designers were being aggressive with difficulty in their encounters  (Cragbeast Queen v1.0 = impossible = my fault!)<br>
3) We were anticipating a level cap increase and associated power gain shortly after the release of Gates<br>
4) Content was created late in the development cycle and we simply ran out of testing time<br>
<br>
I'm sorry that the playerbase's initial taste of Gates was soured by bugs or untuned encounters.  We're still making tweaks to the expansion now, and the retuning we have done has made a world of difference.  In addition to what's already done, we have many more changes lined up to keep the expansion challenging and rewarding while eliminating some of the more frustrating timesinks and imbalances.  <br>
<br>
Most importantly, the above are mistakes that I know we can avoid in the future, and we will.<br>
<br>
-Prathun <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lorileibard>LorileiBard</A></span><br> Posts: 143<br> <font color=#330000>(6/6/04 5:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19472.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Yes its really true</span><hr size=1> I was at the Summit this weekend.  That letter was handed out at the dinner, following Saturdays meetings.  For those of you doubting the authenticity, I have it right here in front of me, and retyped it for the Inny boards.  Other than a few typos, and leaving off of Robert Pfister's name, it's pretty much word for word the same:<br>
<br>
June 5, 2004<br>
<br>
Dear Guild and Community Representatives,<br>
<br>
Thank you very much for a great Summit.  By all accounts it was a huge success.  I can speak for the EverQuest Development Team and tell you that we’re all grateful for the input you provided.  In fact, in trying to generate this list to give to you this evening, we realized there was so much to go over that we wouldn’t be able to get a complete list together in time.  We’re committed to not only listening to your feedback, but working with you to make EverQuest more enjoyable for years to come.<br>
<br>
So, we decided to list the Top Ten themes we would b addressing starting Monday, as well as the most common themes that we’ll come back with more information on by mid-week next week.<br>
<br>
A quick discussion resulted in a list of items that we will immediately address:<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp * Add scripting to shut off empty instances of Plane of Time<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp * Raid message of the day<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp * Improving how we handle beta and the testing process<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp * Increase the number of rebuffs allowed on MOBs<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp * Increase buffs on players through AA’s<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp * Note field on the raid window<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp * Improved consent &amp; drag for raid, group and guild<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp * Improve corpse drag radius<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp * Make charms not no-drop<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp * Guild and individual rewards for guild beta testing<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp * Work on larger To Do list… I know this is a little random<br>
<br>
Future items we will immediately begin looking at and discussing are as follows:<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp * Plane of Time instancing and other issues<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp * Back Flagging solutions to help with High-end guild atrophy<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp * Improved raid and guild functionality<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp * Auto loot all for your corpse<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp * Improvements to Raid XP<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp * Review the Epic 2.0 quests<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp * No more alien NPCs ;-) (focusing more on familiar Norrathian themes)<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp * Solo LDoN-style instances or similar content<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp * Issues with item augmentations<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp * Possible enhancement to Guild Wars<br>
<br>
Of course these aren’t all of [the] items.  You brought us a CD, 2 books, 20 printed sheets, and a manifesto.  We’ll need to go through all of those and our notes before we can really get a good tally of all the wonderful ideas and questions that were presented.<br>
<br>
Thank you again for your feedback and participation.  We’ve had a great weekend and a wonderful display of things to come.<br>
<br>
Sincerely, <br>
Robert Pfister<br>
Executive Producer<br>
EverQuest<br>
<br>
And the EverQuest Development Team!<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lorileibard>LorileiBard</A></span><br> Posts: 144<br> <font color=#330000>(6/6/04 5:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19472.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Yes its really true</span><hr size=1> For those of you who are looking at this list, saying, &quot;well, dang, they left out all THESE issues...&quot;  Please keep in mind what happened.<br>
<br>
The people attending the summit were divided into 5 small groups (10-15 people), each of which met for 4.5 hours over the day to give input to SOE.  That's 22.5 hours worth of meetings.  In each of the meetings I was at, there were always at least 3 SOE employees taking notes.  That's a heck of a lot of notes, on many different suggestions.<br>
<br>
Between the meetings and the dinner, SOE gathered the note takers and came up with a quick &quot;starting&quot; list to hand out to the attendees so they would have something to go home with.  Hence the letter (posted above) handed out at the dinner.<br>
<br>
SOE will be spending the next week organizing the information, prioritizing it into &quot;can be done quickly&quot; and &quot;will take more time&quot; groups, and making sure it gets to the right departments so that they can make the adjustments to make the game more fun for all of us. <p>~Lorilei<br>
